Build and Use Interactions to Navigate Through Product Data

To add interactions that move from one level of data to another, select a widget, click Interaction in the Widget Properties panel, and create a flow. For example, start at a large scale, such as a country, and navigate through more granular areas.

Create an Interaction and Navigate to the Details Page
Select the map widget, click Interaction, and add a flow that navigates from the map to the Details page in the layout.
To let users go back to the default map setting when they deselect a component, select Go back on deselect.

Navigate to the Product Dashboard Data
Add an interaction to navigate to the product dashboard data. In the Details dashboard page, click a repeater widget and create an interaction that navigates to the component page in the layout.
To view this interaction, click Preview and click Fleet (1). This select interaction changes to the Product Details dashboard page (2).

Navigate to a Component Page
Create an interaction on the chart widget that navigates to the component page Details 2 in the layout.
To view this interaction, click Preview and click Count for a name in the table (1). The click interaction navigates to the Account Owner Details dashboard page (2).
The Clear Selection Interaction
Add a Clear Selection interaction to clear queries at any level.
title: Building Interactions in CRM Analytics
